results.name: Decimal expansion of the sum of the reciprocals of squared semiprimes.
comment: Geoffrey Landis and Jonathan Vos Post (personal communication) show that this constant equals ((P2)^2 + P4)/2, where P2 and P4 are constants in A085548 and A085964, respectively.
link: Richard J. Mathar, Series of Reciprocal Powers of k-almost Primes, Table 4.
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Math World: Prime Zeta Function
